<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-14T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="572" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/2740: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Casablanca</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Casablanca</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-14T16:00:00+01:00">January 14, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received January 15—12:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>18. Referring to my 11, January 8, 1 p.m. Possible native
                                demonstration here tomorrow night, thought to be stirred up by
                                certain Nationalists, has been responsible for cancellation all
                                permissions to American officers and enlisted personnel as from noon
                                January 15 for indefinite period.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Algiers as my 4, to Tangier as my 5, and true reading
                                Rabat.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>